                <h2 class="animated fadeInDown">Why Social Distancing?</h2>
                <p class="animated fadeInUp">COVID-19 spreads mainly among people who are in close contact (within about 6 feet) for a prolonged period.Spread happens when an infected person coughs, sneezes, or talks, and droplets from their mouth or nose are launched into the air and land in the mouths or noses of people nearby. The droplets can also be inhaled into the lungs. Recent studies indicate that people who are infected but do not have symptoms likely also play a role in the spread of COVID-19.</p>
